{{infobox football league season|image=|caption=|competition=[[Samoa National League]]|winners=[[Strickland Brothers Lepea|Tuanaimoto Breeze]]|premiers=|promoted=|relegated=|matches=|total goals=|average goals=|league topscorer=|biggest home win=|biggest away win=|highest scoring=|attendance=|average attendance=|prevseason=[[2004 Samoa National League|2004]]|nextseason=[[2006 Samoa National League|2006]]|season=2005}}The '''2005 Samoa National League''', or also known as the '''Upolo First Division''', was the 17th edition of the [[Samoa National League]], the top league of the [[Football Federation Samoa]]. [[Strickland Brothers Lepea|Tuanaimoto Breeze]] won their fourth consecutive title, the first under their new name (original name was ''Strickland Brothers Lepea'').<ref>{{Cite web | url = http://www.rsssf.com/tabless/samoachamp.html | title = Samoa - List of Champions | website = www.rsssf.com | accessdate = 2015-10-30 }}</ref>
