{{infobox country at games | NPC = BUR | NPCname = National Paralympic Committee Burkina Faso | games = Paralympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Burkina Faso|competition=Summer Paralympics|begin_year=|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Burkina Faso]]''' made its [[Paralympic Games]] début at the [[1992 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Barcelona]], sending a tandem of cyclists, a judoka and a weightlifter. The country was represented by a cycling tandem and a powerlifter in [[1996 Summer Paralympics|1996]], and by a single powerlifter in [[2000 Summer Paralympics|2000]]. Burkina Faso did not take part in the [[2004 Summer Paralympics|2004 Games]], but returned to the Paralympics in [[2008 Summer Paralympics|2008]], sending a single cyclist.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=BUR&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Burkina Faso at the Paralympics], [[International Paralympic Committee]]</ref>
Burkina Faso has never taken part in the [[Winter Paralympics]], and no Burkinabé competitor has ever won a Paralympic medal.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=BUR&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Burkina Faso at the Paralympics], International Paralympic Committee</ref>
