{{Infobox football biography | name= Ibor Bakar | fullname = | image = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1986|10|26}} | birth_place = [[Marseille]], France | height = 1.70m | currentclub = [[US Marignane]] | clubnumber = | position = [[Midfielder]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2000–2006 | clubs1 = [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse B]] | caps1 = 7 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2006–2009 | clubs2 = [[GS Consolat]] | caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = 2009–2011 | clubs3 = [[Marignane Gignac F.C.|US Marignane]] | caps3 = 35 | goals3 = 2 | years4 = 2011–2013 | clubs4 = [[AS Gardanne|Gardanne]] | caps4 = | goals4 = | years5 = 2013– | clubs5 = US 1er Canton Marseille 1953 | caps5 = | goals5 = | nationalyears1 = 2007– | nationalteam1 = [[Comoros national football team|Comoros]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | manageryears1 = | managerclubs1 = | pcupdate = 13:47, 7 August 2018 (UTC) | ntupdate = }}
'''Ibor Bakar''' (born 26 October 1986) is a [[Comoros|Comorian]] [[Association football|football]] [[midfielder]], who plays for [[France|French]] [[Championnat de France amateur|fourth division]] side [[US Marignane]]. He also holds French citizenship.
==International career== He has competed with the [[Comoros national football team]], including scoring a goal in a 6–2 loss to [[Madagascar national football team|Madagascar]] in October 2007. The match was the first leg of a preliminary round knockout tie, the winner progressing to the [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]] group stages for [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|2010 World Cup qualification]].
==Personal life== His brother [[Djamel Bakar|Djamel]] plays for [[Ligue 1]] club [[HSC Montpellier|Montpellier]].
