{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Komplett Arena | nickname = | former_names = Komplett.no Arena | image = | location = [[Sandefjord]], [[Norway]] | coordinates = {{coord|59.13725|10.17969|format=dms|source:nowiki_region:NO_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | opened = 21 July 2007 | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = Natural grass | construction_cost = [[Norwegian krone|NOK]] 100 million | architect = | tenants = [[Sandefjord Fotball]] (2007–present) | seating_capacity = 6,582<ref>http://stadiumdb.com/stadiums/nor/storstadion</ref> | record_attendance = 8,103, 21 July 2007 | dimensions = 105 × 68 m }} '''Komplett Arena''' is the current stadium of [[Sandefjord Fotball]]. It was opened on 21 July 2007, when [[FK Lyn|Lyn]] visited Sandefjord, and is still the match with the highest attendance of 8,103. The stadium is named after the club's main sponsor, [[Komplett]].{{cn|date=October 2015}}
