{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Recreation Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Banstead]], [[Surrey]] | establishment = 1840 | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1984 | club1 = [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]] | date = 28 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/291.html Ground profile }}
The '''Recreation Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Banstead]], [[Surrey]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1955, when South Women Second XI played the [[Women's Cricket Association]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/291_misc.html Other matches played on Recreation Ground]</ref> It hosted its only [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match in 1984, when [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]] played [[Cambridge University Cricket Club|Cambridge University]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/291_f.html First-Class Matches played on Recreation Ground]</ref>
Additionally, between 1983 and 2006, the ground played host to a number of Surrey Second XI matches in the [[Second XI Championship]] and Second XI Trophy, hosting a combined total of 20 Second XI matches.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/291_sec.html Second XI Championship Matches played on Recreation Ground]</ref><ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/291_set.html Second XI Trophy Matches played on Recreation Ground]</ref>
The ground has also hosted 2 [[Women's One Day International cricket|Women's One Day International's]]. The first came in 1986 and was played between [[England women's cricket team|England women]] and [[India women's cricket team|India women]]. The second was played between England women and [[Denmark women's cricket team|Denmark women]] in [[1993 Women's Cricket World Cup]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/291_wo.html Women's One-Day International Matches played on Recreation Ground]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, the Recreation Ground is the home venue of [[Banstead Cricket Club]] who play in the [[Surrey Premier League]].<ref>[http://banstead.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp? Banstead Cricket Club]</ref> The original [[cricket pavilion|pavilion]] was constructed in the 1890s and still stands to this day, although a new pavilion was built in the 1970s.
